on%20with%20a%20mission%20to%20host%20arts%20and%20culture%20events%2C%20as%20well%20as%20educational%20programming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPresident%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20first%20lady%20Jacqueline%20Kennedy%20Onassis%20led%20the%20%2430%20million%20fundraising%20campaign%20for%20its%20construction.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223497%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22John%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20Jacqueline%20Kennedy%20at%20a%20fundraising%20event%20for%20the%20National%20Cultural%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69456d7c64858d02d21722b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222623%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20Jacqueline%20Kennedy%20at%20a%20fundraising%20event%20for%20the%20National%20Cultural%20Center%20in%201962.%3Cp%3EBettmann%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20Onassis%20and%20Mamie%20Eisenhower%20served%20as%20honorary%20co-chairwomen%20of%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAfter%20Kennedy's%20assassination%2C%20President%20Lyndon%20Johnson%20signed%20legislation%20renaming%20it%20the%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20Center%20for%20the%20Performing%20Arts.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Lyndon%20Johnson%20signed%20the%20bill%20renaming%20the%20National%20Cultural%20Center%20the%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20Center%20for%20the%20Performing%20Arts%20and%20handed%20the%20pen%20to%20Edward%20Kennedy%2C%20the%20late%20president's%20brother.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69456cac832e0ef1ead68de1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22686%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Lyndon%20Johnson%20signed%20the%20bill%20renaming%20the%20National%20Cultural%20Center%20the%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20Center%20for%20the%20Performing%20Arts%20and%20handed%20the%20pen%20to%20Edward%20Kennedy%2C%20the%20late%20president's%20brother.%3Cp%3EBettmann%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Lyndon%20Johnson%20signed%20the%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20Center%20Act%20in%20January%201964%20to%20change%20the%20name%20and%20provide%20%2423%20million%20in%20federal%20funds%20for%20its%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20signing%20the%20bill%2C%20Johnson%20handed%20the%20pen%20to%20Edward%20Kennedy%2C%20John%20F.%20Kennedy's%20brother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20this%20center%20comes%20to%20reflect%20and%20advance%20the%20greatness%20of%20America%2C%20consider%20then%20those%20glories%20were%20purchased%20by%20a%20valiant%20leader%20who%20never%20swerved%20from%20duty%20%E2%80%94%20John%20Kennedy.%20And%20in%20his%20name%20I%20dedicate%20this%20site%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%20at%20the%20groundbreaking%20ceremony%2C%20held%20in%20December%201964.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Kennedy%20Center%20opened%20on%20September%208%2C%201971.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Kennedy%20Center%20in%201971.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69456e8d04eda4732f2ddbfa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E5%2F1%2F1971%20-%20Washington%2C%20DC%20-%20ORIGINAL%20CAPTION%20READS%3A%20Exterior%20views%20of%20the%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20Center%20for%20the%20Performing%20Arts.%20The%20building%20is%20situated%20at%20river's%20edge%20and%20is%20surrounded%20by%20trees.%3Cp%3EBettmann%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDesigned%20by%20architect%20Edward%20Durell%20Stone%2C%20the%20Kennedy%20Center%20was%20built%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Potomac%20River%20using%203%2C700%20tons%20of%20marble%20gifted%20to%20the%20US%20from%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20opening%20event%2C%20the%20Kennedy%20Center%20hosted%20a%20performance%20of%20%26quot%3BMass%26quot%3B%20by%20Leonard%20Bernstein%2C%20which%20was%20commissioned%20by%20Jacqueline%20Kennedy%20Onassis.%3C%2Fp%3E